What an awesome year 2022 was for me with @kalashnikovusa 

I managed to take home high lady at all the AK events I shot this year! ♥️ 

There were really challenging stages including when I took the KR 103 to Rocky Mountain 3 🔫 and had to shoot out to 500-600 yards in high altitude and extremely dense air not only was it “ballistically difficult” it was hard to carry all the gear on my person and ammo and run up mountains 😅. 

There were hero moments there were zero moments and I am proud to be able to work through all those and learn from all the challenges I am presented with. 

I have learned to adopt and adapt on the fly, take advice from other competitors and friends and apply it to my working knowledge, and explore the capability that the AK platform has in multiple different challenging scenarios. 
 
things I learned:
-If you chrono your ammo and use it from the same case and true your scope to it it will be pretty consistent especially if you have a weather meter/ballistic app that can help you calculate the conditions. 

-AKs get very heavy when they are slung so make sure you have a padded sling 😅 when you have 3 diff mags and have 3 diff guns on you, oh and make sure you work out because some times you will have to offhand targets at long distances and maintain your shots without shaking while carrying your gear 

-have a good support network who you trust to give you sound advice and to be there for you when things or stages don’t go how you hoped they would. Use the 10 min rule. you can be pissed for about 10 min after you mess up a stage but you have to get over it and get to your next stage 

-make sure ALL of your optics are zeroed and check them before every single match, clean your guns, and make sure you have the right lubricant. 

- don’t worry about how others are doing, worry about you. This gets in your head and makes it difficult for you to focus on your own game. Be proud that you’re out there and doing better than the year before 

-Make sure you have great eye pro for any condition, dusty, rainy, bright, dark. This can make or break your target acquisition 

-LOCTITE. i hate loctite but you live and learn the hard way sometimes 😅
All smiles today 😁👍! How about you?

Moving Dry Fire Drill @livefireapp : 

Action- Imagine yourself in the center of a clock. Begin by standing stationary on a position that would be directly in the centerand facing toward the 12 o’clock position. On the start signal of the timer, practice moving while drawing and firing two shots (dry) on the target while continuing to move toward 12 o’clock position. You should have your two dry fire shotsfired within 2-4 steps. Re-center yourself and work your way around the clock moving toward each number on the clock. - @mike.seeklander 

I Was trying to review in video and make sure that as I draw my gun I take a step ensuring that when I am out of the holster I am closer to the target without wasting time so I am able to fire the first shot and then the follow up shot on the second step. Best par time was roughly 1.25 maybe less but I had it set at 1.25. 

Great drill Mike! Can’t wait to try this when it’s not a rainy day outside ! Thanks 🙏

Shooting in a pretty much male dominated sport means you have to prove yourself even more than they do. 
I’ve been met with doubt, criticism, and judgement not only because I’m a woman but because of some of my past choices. But I’ve never failed to prove that I’m there to kick a$$ and take names just like everyone else. 

My journey started almost 3 years ago, I had never shot before then. I immediately jumped into multi 🔫 which required me to learn all 3 platforms, how to maintain them, how to service them and how to get over any kind of issue I may have while on a course. It was very challenging and I still have a lot of work to do to be the very best. 

I have to say multi platform matches are my absolute favorite. The way the matches are ran, the courses of fire, and the ability to play with all 3 platforms makes it challenging and fun.. not only that but extremely rewarding to do well with! 

I have met tons of great people in multi 🔫 and I can’t wait to continue to see all my friends out there when I’m back at competing in them! 

This was from Rocky Mountain 3 🔫 this past summer, it was one of the most challenging multi platform matches I’ve ever shot, on one of the most beautiful I have had the pleasure to compete at. All I have to say is taking an AK that weighs an immense amount with a bi pod, bag and scope on it through terrain at 10k feet and above is quite the challenge.. not to the mention the capability of 762 in those conditions on targets out to 570 yards 😂😳😅..

In so many different posts the past couple of days and opinions I’ve come across, argued, agreed with and disagreed with I have failed to see the dissection of what is truly going on in society. Probably because it’s unpopular to talk about, or will have you “de-platformed” or create a lot of anger toward whoever may be posting it. I’m sure it’s been said but I probably missed it… 

I think this can go 2 ways, as someone who identifies as a libertarian.. I believe in the freedom of personal choice as long as you aren’t harming anyone. I existed in a previous career that I would defend with the same words “I’m not hurting anyone but myself” without realizing or taking into account the wide spread damage that it does create to some physically and some mentally. (An example using myself) I think individualism and personal freedom are paramount to the constitutional rights we have as Americans. But the question I’ve been trying to research and figure out all morning is toxic individualism contradicting morality? I know morality is defined now days by personal belief. But I believe that things have gone a really odd direction in the past 20 years as the morality of society has continually degraded. I’m sure people don’t agree with my beliefs now, that our guns should be taken away and that would solve everything, that my opinion doesn’t matter etc.. but I’m genuinely curious what the solution is when the scale is so tipped the side of extreme immoral individualism being accepted and pushed into necessary societal beliefs? 

I don’t have the answer I’m not even sure if I’m phrasing what is in my mind correctly, but this is what I’ve been thinking about today. 

Sending love and prayers to the Christian families that were lost in the heartless and IMMORAL attack in Nashville.. 

“A sword never kills anybody; it is a tool in the killer’s hand.” 

–Lucius Annaeus Seneca, c. 4BC – 65AD.

How do you adapt to change? 

This is a process that occurs in our brains that is referred to as neuroplasticity, or the capacity for our brain cells to change in response to our behavior, can help us more thoughtfully engage in activities that will contribute to our well-being–no matter our age.

We can influence our brain development in positive or negative directions. The more we engage and challenge our mind and body, the longer our brains function at a high level. There are also many other benefits to encouraging neuroplastic change.

Ways to encourage change your brain: 

⭐️Challenge & Novelty:
A new skill that’s not too easy to learn 

⭐️Intention: 
Learning a skill that has meaning. 
Neuroplastic change is associated with the feeling of being rewarded while engaging in a new task! 

⭐️Specific Attention: 
The skills we practice tend to improve. Focusing on exact tasks increases the likelihood of change.

⭐️Repetition & Intensity: 
One-and-done is not enough. Shorter bouts of intense repetition are usually needed to creating new connections.

⭐️Time:
Be patient with yourself. Neuroplastic change takes time in order for structural and functional change to occur.

I was reading about changing your brain and ways to encourage it and found all these wonderful tips in a great article. You could be doing these things subconsciously and have no idea that you’re practicing and encouraging Neuroplastic change! 
I find that using @livefireapp is doing that for me by creating a consistent way to train and by implementing a mindful and accountable way to practice.

This is a simple multi “platform” drill you can set up and choose any array of targets you want and engage with any amount of ammo. 

I started with AR, transitioned to my open 🔫, then moved to the mag fed 12g. I started with all of them loaded on safe.

When you come across the “Table Start” in competition there is a simple and effective way to make sure you are getting your first shots off quickly.

I wanted to share a passage from my morning reading that I find relevant. 

“There can be no awakening for an inattentive man. He who is content with superficialities never reaches the second stage of unfoldment. This does not mean that some persons are doomed to eternal bondage, merely that all awakening is a consequence of aroused attention.
Nobody remains forever content with superficialities. But some awaken gently while others are rudely roused by painful experiences which force them to consider more attentively the nature of their surroundings.”

Everyone hits a point where they are forced to look at their lives and recognize what is and isn’t working. Some people have to reach rock bottom to gain that perspective. 

Are we caught up in things that don’t matter in the long run? I know I was and have made major life changes in the past couple of years. Simplicity is key. 

So as we go into the holiday season and we are busy working/shopping and receiving.. are we prioritizing and nourishing our relationships or are we caught up in the superficial rat race? 
Do you need to slow down and enjoy?

All worthy questions to ask yourself! 
I am asking myself the same thing
